values: LIFE IS GOOD! so much has happened though....but really no complaints! at all.  Im so tired now....and i still need to study for calc but i just had to say something.

Well, I leave for D.C in 9 hours!  Yes, that means my flight leaves at 6.20.  Stinker.  I'm really excited bc I have no idea what to expect.  I'm hoping to meet alot of fun people and learn lots about Congress (haha).  I'm just happy to have been awarded this experience.  I packed sooo much, maybe I'll have the most clothes there! Pray for some cute boys......
After a week in D.C, my parents are driving up and whisking me of to Virginia...Williamsburg!!

 I'll be home July 2nd...so  Rachel, we have to do something grand for the 4th. I miss you! And if Maggie is home, her too!

 

LOVE YOU

look out Washington....I'm gonna be better than Elle Woods.
O YEAH AND BRAD FROM THE REAL WORLD STOOD BEHIND ME IN SECURITY ON THE WAY HOME.  and he is sooooo hot.  and i was like centimeters away.

Chicago was wonderful as usual.  A day too short though.  After a day of driving up there, we got to the Burnham the next morning.  My parents usually stay at the Burnham so they know everyone, which is nice.  I love that hotel so much, I had forgotten how sweet it is.  I love the Four Seasons in Chicago alot too, but the Burnham's lobby and resturant are so lovely.  It was built like a hundred years ago to be used as office buildings...Al Capone's dentist had his office there.  So, the hallways look like there right out of an old 1930's detective movie...the lobby is all art deco.  It's right in the Loop so the views from all the rooms are awesome.  The first day my mom and I went over to Michigan Avenue and shopped at H&M...that store just fills me with happiness!  We walked along Michigan, just walking into stores. We went to the Bridal Salon at Saks and picked out dresses.
 When we came back to the hotel, I roamed around Filene's and noticed there was an H&M just around the corner from the Burnham...So of course I went in that one too.  I made a fun discovery that I fit in H&M's kid department...found some neat stuff.

 We went out to eat every night, and the last night went to Shaws with my brother and his roommates-really nice guys. It was like eating with three brothers. Also went to the Art Institute, we're members so we go everytime.  I love that place though...its so big there's always something new to look at.  Also went to the Aquarium, something I had never done. My dad gave us an architectual tour which was cute. I love Chicago...the lake, the wide streets, the beautiful buildings.  It's better than New York. 

My brother is now home which is nice. I work all week then leave for D.C.  I'll be exicted soon.

LOVE YOU MISS YOU

My mom took my nanny to the oncologist due to her extremely high white blood count.  The worst case scenerio is leukemia and that can be cured with a new medicine.  It's still scary though.

I'm exhausted from work. ZzZZZZzzzz.  The money is the reward.

*HARRY POTTER! I can't go tomorrow night cuz SAT II and work, but people need to come with me Saturday night! OK?!?

The play is over and I feel really sad (!!!).  Even though it caused me alot of grief, I put alot of my life into this so its hard to comprehend its over.  I feel like this after any play is finished.  Most of the people you spend almost 2 months with you never see again.  WAAAAAHHHHHHHHHHHH. sob, sob.  The worst is the rep cuz then all the people go back to NY broke and jobless.  I just can't do that.  I want to be an actress but the temping life just isn't for me.  (temping=transitional jobs, not permanent ie secretarial, nannies).  Eck.  That really, really freaks me out.   I know I will finish high school, I know I will go to college, but then what?????  In the back of my head I dream that during college I will land a job and won't have to finish.  Then, I could just go back to school or finish it in between jobs ala Julia Stiles.

This guy who was in the play, a 19 year old college student, the last 2 days of the show, we started talking backstage and physically flirting (stupid stuff like grabbing each other when the other would walk by).  And then the last two performances Sat., he started sitting by me whenever he wasn't on stage, we hung out during intermission, just talking and finding ways to touch each other (it sounds gross but it isn't i swear!!!).  The last fucking day.  Said I was cute.  Only if I were older.  Struck the set, carried stuff out to his car.  Hugged him goodbye, knew we would never see each other again.

And, big surprise, like always, I feel nasty and gross just talking about it.  WHAT IS WRONG WITH ME?  I had a crush on him, started talking to him, then he starts talking to me, sitting by me when there are plenty of places to sit, holding my hand and I feel gross!!! like i always do when guys start paying attention to me.  I feel happy for awhile but then I'm like gross! get away from me! and I get annoyed by them.  I know if the show had more performances, I would stop talking to him.
I've got a crush! or maybe two!! Yes!
